race.comment: Interesting race where 3rd, 4th and 5th from a race at Geelong clash with some who are coming off impressive trial performances. REGAL RIPPER (2) was first home of those coming out of the Geelong race, which was his debut, so you'd expect he'll be better for that outing. SOUTH YARRA BELLE (10) is another coming off an impressive jumpout win and her debut was a total forgive when held up back in the field in a quickly-run race. Comes right into it from the low draw. TAUPE (12) was weak late at Geelong but that was a heavy track on debut, so happy to give another chance. ARABELLA STAR (5) is the other out of the Geelong race and she was the strongest late so she'll be hitting the line hard again.
